Here's a JavaScript function that uses regex to extract the three character code from the provided filename:

```javascript
function getCodeFromFilename(filename) {
  const pattern = /([0-9A-Za-z]{3})(\.usfm)$/;
  const match = pattern.exec(filename);
  if (match && match[1]) {
    return match[1];
  }
}
```

The `pattern` variable is a regular expression that matches a group of three characters (either digits or letters) followed by the filename extension ".usfm". The `exec()` method is called on this pattern to extract the matched string. If a match is found, the function returns the first captured group (which contains the three character code).

Note that if there's no match, the function will return `undefined`.
